</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C348651FFFF477524AAEF9923420F8F7" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED3694FFF477524AAEF9923420F8F7" blockId="12.[151,1437,950,1733]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFF477524AAEF992345AF86B" bold="true" box="[199,315,1599,1625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Remarks.</emphasis>
The smallest Indian 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D17FFF477524842F99237ABF86B" authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1833" box="[555,714,1599,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFF477524842F99237ABF86B" box="[555,714,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">Pheropsophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded. It is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D17FFF477524EC6F9ED305EF86B" authorityName="Arrow" authorityYear="1901" box="[1199,1343,1599,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFF477524EC6F9ED305EF86B" box="[1199,1343,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="77">P. nigricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by having head bi-coloured with anterior yellow and posterior black, broad lateral bead of pronotum, obliterate humerus without spot, with median spot instead of median transverse band. Endemic to Eastern Himalaya hotspot of biodiversity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
